---

Pour the @water{300%ml for the rice} into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn 
the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and 
leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue 
to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (stalks and all).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced). 
Separate the shallot slices.

In a #small bowl{}, combine the shallot slices and @plain flour{1%tbsp}. Toss until coated.

Meanwhile, pour enough @oil{} into a #large saucepan{} to cover the bottom, then pop it on 
medium-high heat. TIP: Check if the oil is hot enough by adding one shallot slice - if it 
sizzles, it's ready.

Add the shallot slices to the pan. Fry until golden and crispy, ~{2-4%minutes}. Turn once 
or twice, then remove with a #slotted spoon{} and transfer to some #kitchen paper{} to 
absorb any excess oil.

In another small bowl, combine the cooled crispy shallots and parsley. Set your curry 
topping aside.

Wipe out the shallot frying pan and pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the @THIS™ Isn't Chicken Plant-Based Pieces{170%g} to the pan and fry until 
golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}.

Add the @tikka masala paste{75%g}, @tomato puree{30%g} and garlic to the (now empty) pan 
with a drizzle of oil if needed. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1%tbsp} and @water{100%ml for the curry} to 
the pan. Stir to combine, bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer until the sauce 
has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once thickened, add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted, 
~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the cooked THIS™ Isn't Chicken and @creme fraiche{150%ml}. Taste and season 
with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed, adding a splash of water if it's a little 
thick. Simmer until piping hot, ~{2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice using a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with your ultimate THIS™ Isn't Chicken tikka.

Sprinkle over the shallot and parsley topping to finish.

Enjoy!